'''搖籃曲'''（''Berceuse''），[[作品号|Op.]] 57，為[[弗雷德里克·肖邦|蕭邦]]於1843-1844年所作的一首[[搖籃曲|搖籃曲]]<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Berceuse|author=|url=https://doi-org.wikipedialibrary.idm.oclc.org/10.1093/gmo/9781561592630.article.02749|last=Hamilton|first=Kenneth L.|date=2001|journal=[[Grove_Music_Online|Grove Music Online]]|publisher=[[Oxford_University_Press|Oxford University Press]]|doi=10.1093/gmo/9781561592630.article.02749}}</ref>，並於1844年出版，獻給埃莉斯·加瓦尔（Élise Gavard）。此曲為[[降D大調|降D大調]]，[[行板|行板]]，6/8拍。

在1843年夏開始創作時，蕭邦在[[诺昂-维克|诺昂-维克]]與[[乔治·桑|喬治‧桑]]一起。由於其手稿最初由{{link-en|寶琳·維亞朵|Pauline Viardot}}保管，此曲可能受到她小女兒露易絲啟發，當時因其母在維也納巡迴演唱而由兩人照顧。<ref>{{cite book|author=焦元溥|title=聽見蕭邦|url=//books.google.com.hk/books?id=FiJxCgAAQBAJ|date=2010年5月|publisher=聯經|isbn=978-957-08-3570-0|pages=176}}</ref>此曲的旋律近似歌曲「月已升起，狗已沉睡」（Już miesiąć zeszedł, psy się uśpily），可能蕭邦創作此曲時亦回憶起它，而事實上他於其作品Op. 13已用到此歌旋律。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.chopin.nifc.pl/chopin/composition/detail/id/121|title=The Fryderyk Chopin Institute: Compositions: Berceuse|accessdate=2013-08-12|archive-date=2020-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922183729/https://en.chopin.nifc.pl/chopin/composition/detail/id/121|dead-url=no}}</ref>

整個作品以十六首以四小節為單位的變奏串連，中間沒有停頓分隔。最初蕭邦將它題為[[變奏曲|變奏曲]]，而且在最初起草時亦替各變奏編號，但為了出版改名為搖籃曲（Berceuse）。<ref name="Samson">{{cite book| last = Samson| first = Jim| url = https://www.hyperion-records.co.uk/tw.asp?w=W378| title = Berceuse in D flat major, Op 57| publisher = [[Hyperion_Records|Hyperion Records]]| year = 2008| accessdate = 2018-09-11| archive-date = 2019-03-29| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190329150531/https://www.hyperion-records.co.uk/tw.asp?w=W378| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="Nowik">{{cite book| last = Nowik| first = Wojciech| chapter-url = https://books.google.de/books?id=jUs9AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA40&lpg=PA25| chapter = Fryderyk Chopin's op. 57 – from Variantes to Berceuse| title = Chopin Studies 1| publisher = [[Cambridge_University_Press|Cambridge University Press]]| year = 1988| isbn = 9780521303651| pages = 25–40| access-date = 2019-03-29| archive-date = 2019-03-29| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190329161247/https://books.google.de/books?id=jUs9AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA40&lpg=PA25| dead-url = no}}</ref>其左手部分為固定音型伴奏，只在近結尾處有所變化。右手則為優美而繁複的樂句，令人聯想到他早期的華麗風格。<ref name="Eigeldinger">{{cite book| last = Eigeldinger| first = Jean-Jacques| editor-last = Rink| editor-first = John| editor2-last = Samson| editor2-first = Jim| chapter-url = https://books.google.com/books?id=UVVqMCoeJIkC&pg=PA114| chapter = Placing Chopin: Reflections on a Compositional Aesthetic| title = Chopin Studies 2| publisher = [[Cambridge_University_Press|Cambridge University Press]]| year = 1994| isbn = 9780521034333}}</ref>全曲以弱音奏出，其變化主要由織體及音色塑造，這一方面相信亦引起[[德彪西|德彪西]]對此曲的興趣。<ref name="Samson"/>

